      Working with the Government of Japan, our Japanese partner team built <a href="http://www.actaba.jp">Actaba</a>, a tool to create automatic polygons to track farmlands and calculate their utilization. We are able to calculate the NDVI (Normalized Difference
      Vegetation Index) and help farmers to find the optimal time to harvest a
      particular crop.
    </p>

    <p>
      Actaba is a result of our technology that uses satellite imagery backed data
      provided by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JAXA">JAXA</a> (Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency) and <a href="https://www.restek.com">RESTEC</a> (Remote
